o
re the liability becomes enforceable and the limitations must be observed.  The letter upon which the plaintiff depends contains no express promise either conditional or unconditional, restricted or unrestricted.  But, although a document relied upon as a
n acknowledgement contained no express promise, it may effect a revival of the debtor\rquote s liability if there is found in it a distinct admission of the debt.\'94
